(1, 1, 1, 'India bans 59 Chinese apps, including TikTok, ShareIt, UC Browser', '<h3>Breaking News: Major Tech Ban</h3><p>The <strong>Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology (MeitY)</strong> on Monday banned <em>59 Chinese apps</em>, including Bytedance\'s TikTok, Alibaba\'s UC Browser, Tencent\'s WeChat, and Baidu Map, saying these pose a threat to the <strong>\"sovereignty and integrity of India\"</strong>.</p><h4>Key Points:</h4><ul><li>59 Chinese applications banned</li><li>Includes popular apps like TikTok, UC Browser, and WeChat</li><li>Action taken under Section 69A of IT Act</li><li>Response to Galwan valley face-off</li></ul><p>The move to ban these apps was taken after the recent face-off at Galwan valley between India and China. Officials stated that the action was necessary to <u>protect national security</u> and user data privacy.</p><blockquote>\"This decision is crucial for India\'s sovereignty and data protection,\" said a senior government official.</blockquote><p>The ban affects millions of users across the country who have been using these applications for entertainment, communication, and business purposes.</p>', 'article-1-1616580787.webp', '2021-03-24', 0, 1),
(4, 1, 3, 'US election 2020: Trump and Biden locked in tight White House race', '<h2>US Presidential Election 2020: A Nail-Biting Race</h2><p><strong>Donald Trump</strong> and his Democratic rival <strong>Joe Biden</strong> have been locked in a <em>tight race</em> for the White House, with the Republican narrowly ahead in a few key states that could decide the winner.</p><h4>Current Situation:</h4><p>The latest vote tally shows the Republican president a few points ahead in several crucial swing states:</p><ol><li>North Carolina</li><li>Georgia</li><li>Pennsylvania</li><li>Michigan</li><li>Wisconsin</li></ol><p>These <u>handful of swing states</u> will ultimately determine the result of this historic election.</p><h4>What Experts Say:</h4><blockquote>\"This is one of the most closely contested elections in recent history. Every vote counts, and we may not know the final result for several days.\"</blockquote><p>Both campaigns have mobilized their supporters for what could be a <strong>historic finish</strong> to this election cycle.</p>', 'article-1-1616580787.webp', '2021-03-24', 0, 1),
(6, 2, 1, 'OnePlus 8T Cyberpunk 2077 Limited Edition launched in India', '<h3>üéÆ Gaming Meets Premium Smartphones</h3><p><strong>OnePlus</strong> has launched the limited edition <em>OnePlus 8T Cyberpunk 2077 Edition</em> in India at a competitive price of <strong>Rs 42,999</strong>.</p><h4>Technical Specifications:</h4><ul><li><strong>RAM:</strong> 12GB</li><li><strong>Storage:</strong> 256GB internal storage</li><li><strong>Theme:</strong> Cyberpunk 2077 custom design</li><li><strong>Special packaging</strong> with themed accessories</li></ul><p>The phone was first launched in <u>China last week</u> with a retail box bundled with several accessories themed after the highly anticipated <em>Cyberpunk 2077 video game</em>.</p><h4>What Makes It Special?</h4><p>This <strong>limited edition</strong> variant features:</p><ol><li>Exclusive Cyberpunk 2077 wallpapers and themes</li><li>Custom UI elements inspired by the game</li><li>Special edition packaging and accessories</li><li>Collector\'s certificate of authenticity</li></ol><blockquote>\"This collaboration brings together the best of gaming and mobile technology,\" said OnePlus spokesperson.</blockquote>', 'article-2-1616580598.jpg', '2021-03-24', 0, 1),
(7, 2, 1, 'OnePlus 8T launched in India: Price, specs and everything else you need to know', '<h2>üì± OnePlus 8T: The New Flagship Has Arrived!</h2><p><strong>OnePlus</strong> today unveiled its latest flagship smartphone, the <em>OnePlus 8T</em>, in India at a starting price of <strong>Rs 42,999</strong> for the 8GB RAM and 128GB storage variant.</p><h3>Key Features:</h3><h4>Display Excellence</h4><ul><li><strong>Screen Size:</strong> 6.55-inch Fluid AMOLED display</li><li><strong>Refresh Rate:</strong> 120Hz for smooth scrolling</li><li><strong>Resolution:</strong> Full HD+ with HDR10+ support</li></ul><h4>Camera System</h4><p>The OnePlus 8T comes equipped with a <strong>quad-camera setup</strong> at the back:</p><ol><li>48MP primary sensor with OIS</li><li>16MP ultra-wide lens</li><li>5MP macro camera</li><li>2MP monochrome sensor</li></ol><h4>‚ö° Warp Charge 65 Technology</h4><p>One of the <u>standout features</u> is the <strong>Warp Charge 65</strong> fast charging technology that can:</p><ul><li>Charge 0-100% in just <strong>39 minutes</strong></li><li>Provide day-long power with 15 minutes of charging</li><li>Industry-leading charging speeds</li></ul><blockquote>\"The OnePlus 8T represents our commitment to providing flagship experiences at accessible prices,\" said OnePlus India team.</blockquote><h4>Additional Highlights:</h4><p>Other notable features include <em>5G connectivity</em>, stereo speakers, and <strong>OxygenOS 11</strong> based on Android 11.</p>', 'article-2-1620564684.webp', '2021-03-24', 1, 1),
(17, 8, 3, 'Aftab chopped Shraddha into 35 pieces, hid them in new fridge for almost 3 weeks: Police', '<h2>‚ö†Ô∏è Delhi Murder Case: Shocking Details Emerge</h2><p><strong>Aftab Amin Poonawala</strong> allegedly <em>strangled his live-in partner</em> <strong>Shraddha Walkar</strong> to death and sawed her body into <u>35 pieces</u> in a horrific crime that has shocked the nation.</p><h4>Key Details of the Investigation:</h4><ul><li>Body parts stored in a <strong>300-litre refrigerator</strong></li><li>Kept at his <em>Mehrauli residence</em> in South Delhi</li><li>Stored for almost <strong>three weeks</strong></li><li>Disposed across the city over several days</li></ul><p>Delhi Police officials revealed that the accused planned and executed this <strong>heinous crime</strong> with disturbing precision.</p><h4>Investigation Progress:</h4><p>Authorities are conducting extensive searches and have recovered several pieces of evidence from multiple locations across the city. <em>Forensic teams</em> are working to gather more details.</p><blockquote>\"This is one of the most brutal crimes we have investigated. The accused showed no remorse,\" said a senior police official.</blockquote><p>‚ö†Ô∏è The case has raised serious concerns about <strong>domestic violence</strong> and the safety of individuals in live-in relationships.</p>', 'article-8-1616578937.webp', '2021-04-03', 0, 1),
(19, 8, 2, 'Delhi air quality deteriorates to \'very poor\' category after slight respite', '<h2>üå´Ô∏è Delhi Air Quality Crisis: Pollution Levels Spike Again</h2><p>After a <em>brief improvement</em>, Delhi\'s air quality has <strong>deteriorated sharply</strong> and slipped back to the <u>\'very poor\' category</u> on Tuesday, according to <strong>Central Pollution Control Board (CPCB)</strong> data.</p><h4>Current Air Quality Status:</h4><ul><li><strong>Current AQI:</strong> 314 (recorded at 8 AM Tuesday)</li><li><strong>Previous Day AQI:</strong> 249 (Monday)</li><li><strong>Category:</strong> Very Poor üò∑</li><li><strong>Increase:</strong> 65 points in 24 hours</li></ul><h3>Understanding AQI Categories:</h3><p>The Air Quality Index provides a standardized measure of air pollution levels:</p><ol><li><strong>0-50:</strong> Good üü¢</li><li><strong>51-100:</strong> Satisfactory üü°</li><li><strong>101-200:</strong> Moderate üü†</li><li><strong>201-300:</strong> Poor üî¥</li><li><strong>301-400:</strong> Very Poor üü£</li><li><strong>401-500:</strong> Severe ‚ö´</li></ol><blockquote>"Citizens should limit outdoor activities and wear masks when venturing outside. People with respiratory conditions need to take extra precautions," advised health officials.</blockquote><p>The <strong>worsening air quality</strong> has renewed concerns about public health, particularly for vulnerable groups including children, elderly, and those with <em>pre-existing respiratory conditions</em>.</p>', 'article-8-1616578990.jpg', '2021-04-01', 1, 1),
(20, 8, 3, 'After Bengaluru barber tests COVID-19 positive, 111 primary contacts quarantined', '<h2>ü¶† COVID-19 Alert: Mass Quarantine in Bengaluru</h2><p>A day after a <strong>barber in Bengaluru\'s Malleshwaram area</strong> tested positive for the <em>novel coronavirus</em>, the city civic body has taken <u>immediate action</u> by quarantining <strong>111 people</strong> connected to the case.</p><h4>Quarantine Breakdown:</h4><ul><li><strong>Primary Contacts:</strong> 60 individuals</li><li><strong>Secondary Contacts:</strong> 51 individuals</li><li><strong>Total Quarantined:</strong> 111 people</li><li><strong>Location:</strong> Malleshwaram area, Bengaluru</li></ul><h4>BBMP Response:</h4><p>The <strong>Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP)</strong> swiftly responded to contain potential spread:</p><ol><li>Identified and traced all primary contacts</li><li>Collected swab samples from all 60 primary contacts</li><li>Quarantined both primary and secondary contacts</li><li>Results are currently awaited</li></ol><blockquote>"We are taking all necessary precautions to prevent community transmission. Contact tracing is ongoing," said BBMP health officials.</blockquote><p>The case highlights the importance of <em>rapid contact tracing</em> and <strong>immediate quarantine measures</strong> in controlling COVID-19 spread in densely populated urban areas. üò∑</p>', 'article-8-1620575059.jpg', '2021-03-31', 0, 1),
(28, 3, 3, 'How to make Hyderabadi Dum Ka Murgh', '<h2>üçó Hyderabadi Dum Ka Murgh: A Royal Delicacy</h2><p><strong>Hyderabadi Dum Ka Murgh</strong> is a <em>traditional dish</em> from the <u>royal kitchens of Hyderabad</u>. This aromatic chicken curry is <strong>slow-cooked</strong> with a blend of spices, yogurt, and saffron, resulting in tender meat with a rich, flavorful gravy.</p><h3>The Art of Dum Cooking:</h3><p>The <strong>\'dum\' cooking technique</strong> is what makes this dish special. It involves <em>sealing the pot with dough</em> to trap the steam, allowing the flavors to meld beautifully over slow heat.</p><h4>Key Ingredients:</h4><ul><li>üêî <strong>Chicken:</strong> 1 kg, preferably with bones</li><li><strong>Yogurt:</strong> 1 cup, whisked</li><li><strong>Saffron:</strong> A pinch, soaked in warm milk</li><li><strong>Onions:</strong> 2 large, thinly sliced</li><li><strong>Ginger-Garlic Paste:</strong> 2 tablespoons</li><li><strong>Spices:</strong> Cardamom, cinnamon, cloves, bay leaves</li><li><strong>Red Chili Powder:</strong> 1 tsp</li><li><strong>Fresh Coriander & Mint:</strong> For garnish</li></ul><h4>Cooking Steps:</h4><ol><li>Marinate chicken with yogurt, spices, and saffron for 2 hours</li><li>Fry onions until golden brown</li><li>Layer marinated chicken in a heavy-bottomed pot</li><li>Top with fried onions and fresh herbs</li><li>Seal the pot with dough</li><li>Cook on low heat for 45-60 minutes</li></ol><blockquote>"The secret to authentic Hyderabadi Dum Ka Murgh lies in patience and the quality of spices used," says Chef Imran from Hyderabad.</blockquote><p>Perfect for <strong>special occasions</strong> and <em>family gatherings</em>, this dish is best served with naan or basmati rice. üë®‚Äçüç≥</p>', 'article-3-1616581072.jpg', '2021-03-25', 1, 1),
(29, 3, 2, 'Mumbai street food: A journey through flavors', '<h2>üåÜ Mumbai Street Food: A Culinary Journey</h2><p>Mumbai\'s <strong>street food culture</strong> is <em>legendary</em>, offering an <u>explosion of tastes</u> from vada pav to pani puri. Each dish tells a story of the city\'s <strong>diverse culinary heritage</strong>, blending influences from various communities.</p><h3>Iconic Mumbai Street Foods:</h3><h4>The Classics:</h4><ul><li>ü•î <strong>Vada Pav:</strong> Mumbai\'s beloved spicy potato burger</li><li>üíß <strong>Pani Puri:</strong> Crispy shells filled with tangy water</li><li><strong>Bhel Puri:</strong> Crunchy rice puff mixture with chutneys</li><li><strong>Pav Bhaji:</strong> Buttery bread with spiced vegetable mash</li><li><strong>Sev Puri:</strong> Crispy base loaded with toppings</li></ul><h4>Popular Street Food Locations:</h4><ol><li><strong>Chowpatty Beach:</strong> Famous for spicy bhel puri and ice golas</li><li><strong>Colaba Lanes:</strong> Home to the buttery pav bhaji stalls</li><li><strong>Juhu Beach:</strong> Evening food festival atmosphere</li><li><strong>Mohammed Ali Road:</strong> Ramadan food paradise</li></ol><h3>The Cultural Significance:</h3><p>From the <em>spicy bhel puri</em> at <strong>Chowpatty Beach</strong> to the <em>buttery pav bhaji</em> in lanes of <strong>Colaba</strong>, Mumbai\'s street food is an <u>experience that awakens all senses</u>. üòã</p><blockquote>"Mumbai street food is not just about eating, it\'s about experiencing the soul of the city. Each vendor has perfected their recipe over generations," says food historian Rashmi Shah.</blockquote><p>Food vendors have <strong>perfected these recipes over generations</strong>, making each bite a testament to Mumbai\'s rich food culture and the dedication of its street food artisans. üç¥</p>', 'article-3-1616581173.jpg', '2021-03-26', 0, 1),
(37, 4, 2, 'How online classes are bringing challenges to the education system', '<h2>üíª Online Education: Navigating New Challenges</h2><p>Since schools opened with the help of <strong>technology and online classes</strong>, <em>significant challenges</em> have emerged that impact the quality of education delivery.</p><h4>Major Challenges Identified:</h4><h3>1. Infrastructure Gap</h3><p>A major challenge is that <u>most schools are not geared</u> towards this way of learning because the <strong>infrastructure of online mode</strong> is not quite as available as offline mode.</p><ul><li><strong>Limited Internet Connectivity:</strong> Many areas lack stable broadband</li><li><strong>Device Shortage:</strong> Not all students have access to computers or tablets</li><li><strong>Power Supply Issues:</strong> Frequent outages disrupt online sessions</li><li><strong>Digital Literacy:</strong> Teachers and students need training</li></ul><h3>2. Resource Distribution Inequality</h3><p>The second biggest challenge has been in the hands of the <em>government</em> to <strong>equally distribute resources</strong> to everyone to close the gap of online learning.</p><ol><li>Urban vs rural divide in infrastructure</li><li>Economic barriers to accessing technology</li><li>Lack of technical support systems</li><li>Insufficient digital content in regional languages</li></ol><blockquote>"The digital divide has widened educational inequalities. We must ensure that every student, regardless of their location or economic background, has access to quality online education," said education expert Dr. Sharma.</blockquote><p>Addressing these challenges is <strong>crucial</strong> for ensuring <em>equitable access</em> to education for all students. üìö</p>', 'article-4-1616582091.webp', '2021-04-26', 1, 1),
(38, 3, 3, 'Why it is important to have white onions in summer', '<h2>üßÖ White Onions: Summer\'s Superfood</h2><p>A <strong>powerhouse of antioxidants</strong>, white onions are <em>essential</em> for maintaining health during the <u>hot summer months</u>.</p><h3>Nutritional Benefits:</h3><h4>Rich in Essential Nutrients</h4><p>White onions are <strong>rich in Vitamin C</strong> and also have:</p><ul><li>ü¶† <strong>Anti-bacterial properties:</strong> Fight harmful bacteria</li><li><strong>Anti-fungal properties:</strong> Prevent fungal infections</li><li><strong>Anti-inflammatory properties:</strong> Reduce inflammation</li></ul><h4>Sulfur Compounds for Detoxification</h4><p>The presence of <em>sulfur compounds</em> help <strong>detoxify the body</strong> naturally, flushing out toxins and supporting liver function.</p><h3>Health Benefits:</h3><ol><li><strong>Blood Sugar Control:</strong> Help reduce blood sugar levels</li><li><strong>Bone Health:</strong> Improve bone density and strength</li><li><strong>Cancer Prevention:</strong> Have anti-cancer properties</li><li><strong>Immunity Boost:</strong> Phytonutrients enhance immune system</li><li><strong>Digestive Health:</strong> Fiber content keeps digestive system healthy</li></ol><h4>Why Summer is Special?</h4><p>During summer, white onions provide <strong>cooling effects</strong> and help maintain <em>hydration levels</em> while offering protection against seasonal infections.</p><blockquote>"Incorporating white onions in your summer diet can significantly improve overall health. Their natural cooling properties make them ideal for hot weather," advises nutritionist Dr. Priya Mehta.</blockquote><p>Add white onions to salads, raitas, and curries for <u>maximum health benefits</u>! ü•ó</p>', 'article-3-1616581275.webp', '2021-04-26', 0, 1),
(39, 1, 5, 'Parliament passes landmark bill for electoral reforms', '<h2>üèõÔ∏è Electoral Reforms: Parliament Passes Landmark Legislation</h2><p>The <strong>Lok Sabha</strong> today passed a <em>significant electoral reform bill</em> aimed at increasing <u>transparency in political funding</u> and candidate selection.</p><h4>Key Provisions of the Bill:</h4><ul><li><strong>Stricter Disclosure Norms:</strong> Political parties must reveal income sources</li><li><strong>Expenditure Tracking:</strong> Detailed reporting of campaign spending required</li><li><strong>Candidate Background:</strong> Enhanced disclosure of criminal records</li><li><strong>Funding Transparency:</strong> New mechanisms for tracking donations</li></ul><h3>Parliamentary Debates:</h3><p>Opposition parties raised <em>concerns about certain provisions</em>, leading to <strong>heated debates</strong> that lasted several hours. Key points of contention included:</p><ol><li>Implementation timeline and mechanisms</li><li>Enforcement penalties for non-compliance</li><li>Privacy concerns regarding donor information</li><li>Impact on smaller regional parties</li></ol><h4>Next Steps:</h4><p>The bill will now be sent to the <strong>Rajya Sabha</strong> for further deliberation and approval before becoming law.</p><blockquote>"This legislation represents a major step toward cleaner politics and greater accountability. Transparency in political funding is essential for a healthy democracy," said the Law Minister.</blockquote><p>Political analysts view this as a <u>watershed moment</u> in India\'s electoral reform journey. üó≥Ô∏è</p>', 'article-1-1616580787.webp', '2021-04-15', 1, 1),
(40, 1, 6, 'State elections witness record voter turnout', '<h2>üó≥Ô∏è Record Voter Turnout in State Elections</h2><p>Multiple <strong>state assembly elections</strong> concluded today with an <em>unprecedented voter turnout</em> of <strong>72%</strong>, marking the <u>highest participation</u> in the last two decades.</p><h3>Success Factors:</h3><ul><li><strong>Awareness Campaigns:</strong> Extensive voter education programs</li><li><strong>Improved Infrastructure:</strong> More polling booths in remote areas</li><li><strong>Technology Integration:</strong> Smooth EVM operations</li><li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Special provisions for elderly and disabled voters</li></ul><h4>Key Issues That Drove Voters:</h4><p>Political analysts suggest that several pressing issues dominated <em>voter sentiment</em>:</p><ol><li>üíº <strong>Unemployment:</strong> Job creation and economic opportunities</li><li>üåæ <strong>Agricultural Reforms:</strong> Farmer welfare policies</li><li>üèØ <strong>Healthcare:</strong> Access to quality medical services</li><li>üè≠ <strong>Education:</strong> Improving schools and colleges</li></ol><blockquote>"This historic turnout reflects the maturity of Indian democracy and citizens\' commitment to participatory governance," said Chief Election Commissioner.</blockquote><p><strong>Final results</strong> are expected within <u>48 hours</u> after counting concludes. üèÜ</p>', 'article-1-1616580787.webp', '2021-05-02', 0, 1),
(41, 2, 7, 'India launches ambitious 5G rollout plan', '<h2>üì∂ India\'s 5G Revolution Begins</h2><p>The government today unveiled its <strong>comprehensive strategy</strong> for <em>5G network deployment</em> across major cities by the <u>end of this year</u>.</p><h3>Investment & Infrastructure:</h3><h4>Major Financial Commitment:</h4><ul><li><strong>Total Investment:</strong> Over Rs 50,000 crores</li><li><strong>Telecom Operators:</strong> All major players participating</li><li><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> New cell towers and fiber optic networks</li><li><strong>Timeline:</strong> Phase 1 complete by December 2021</li></ul><h3>Transformative Impact:</h3><p>The <strong>high-speed 5G network</strong> promises to revolutionize multiple sectors:</p><ol><li>üèØ <strong>Healthcare:</strong> Telemedicine and remote surgery capabilities</li><li>üéì <strong>Education:</strong> Immersive AR/VR learning experiences</li><li>üè≠ <strong>Manufacturing:</strong> Smart factories and IoT integration</li><li>üöó <strong>Automotive:</strong> Connected and autonomous vehicles</li><li>üèõÔ∏è <strong>Smart Cities:</strong> Enhanced urban infrastructure</li></ol><h4>Rollout Strategy:</h4><p>Urban areas will be covered first, with <em>rural areas</em> included in <strong>subsequent phases</strong> over the next three years.</p><blockquote>"5G will be a game-changer for India\'s digital economy. It will create new opportunities, enhance productivity, and improve quality of life for citizens," stated the Telecom Minister.</blockquote><p>This positions India among <u>global leaders</u> in 5G adoption. üáÆüá≥</p>', 'article-2-1616580598.jpg', '2021-04-20', 1, 1),
(42, 2, 8, 'Major tech company announces AI-powered smartphone', '<h2>ü§ñ AI-Powered Smartphone: The Future is Here</h2><p>A leading smartphone manufacturer has revealed its <strong>latest flagship device</strong> featuring <em>advanced artificial intelligence capabilities</em> that redefine mobile experiences.</p><h3>Revolutionary AI Features:</h3><h4>Smart Battery Management</h4><ul><li>üîã <strong>Adaptive Power:</strong> Machine learning optimizes battery usage</li><li><strong>Usage Prediction:</strong> AI learns user patterns</li><li><strong>Intelligent Charging:</strong> Extends battery lifespan</li></ul><h4>Enhanced Photography</h4><p>The <strong>AI camera system</strong> delivers professional-grade photos:</p><ol><li><strong>Scene Recognition:</strong> Automatically detects 100+ scenarios</li><li><strong>Night Mode AI:</strong> Exceptional low-light performance</li><li><strong>Portrait Enhancement:</strong> Intelligent bokeh and beautification</li><li><strong>Video Stabilization:</strong> Real-time AI processing</li></ol><h4>Personalized User Experience</h4><ul><li><strong>Smart Assistant:</strong> Context-aware AI companion</li><li><strong>App Prediction:</strong> Launches apps before you need them</li><li><strong>Adaptive UI:</strong> Interface adjusts to usage patterns</li></ul><h3>Market Availability:</h3><p>Industry experts believe this marks a <u>significant leap</u> in mobile technology. The device will be available <strong>worldwide starting next month</strong> at a competitive price point.</p><blockquote>"This smartphone represents the convergence of hardware and AI software. It doesn\'t just respond to users‚Äîit anticipates their needs," said the company\'s CEO.</blockquote>', 'article-2-1620564684.webp', '2021-05-05', 1, 1),
(43, 2, 1, 'Cybersecurity threats increase by 40% in financial sector', '<h2>üîí Cybersecurity Alert: Financial Sector Under Siege</h2><p>A recent report highlights a <strong>dramatic surge</strong> in <em>cyberattacks targeting banks</em> and financial institutions, with a <u>40% increase</u> compared to last year.</p><h3>Common Attack Methods:</h3><ul><li>üé£ <strong>Phishing:</strong> Fraudulent emails and fake websites</li><li>üîê <strong>Ransomware:</strong> Data encryption and extortion demands</li><li><strong>Malware:</strong> Malicious software infiltration</li><li><strong>Social Engineering:</strong> Manipulating employees</li></ul><h4>Industry Response:</h4><p>Security experts emphasize the <strong>urgent need</strong> for robust defense mechanisms:</p><ol><li><strong>Employee Training:</strong> Regular cybersecurity awareness programs</li><li><strong>Multi-Factor Authentication:</strong> Enhanced login security</li><li><strong>AI-Powered Monitoring:</strong> Real-time threat detection</li><li><strong>Incident Response Plans:</strong> Quick action protocols</li></ol><h3>Major Investments:</h3><p>Several major banks have already invested <em>millions in upgrading</em> their cybersecurity infrastructure, including:</p><ul><li>Advanced firewalls and intrusion detection systems</li><li>Security Operations Centers (SOC)</li><li>Regular penetration testing</li><li>Encrypted communication channels</li></ul><blockquote>"The financial sector is the most targeted by cybercriminals. Continuous vigilance and investment in security infrastructure is non-negotiable," warned cybersecurity expert Dr. Kumar.</blockquote><p>Regulatory authorities are considering <strong>stricter compliance requirements</strong> to protect customer data. ‚ö†Ô∏è</p>', 'article-2-1616580598.jpg', '2021-04-28', 0, 1),
(44, 2, 9, 'Space agency successfully tests reusable rocket technology', '<h2>üöÄ Historic Achievement: Reusable Rocket Technology Tested</h2><p>The national space agency achieved a <strong>major milestone</strong> by successfully testing a <em>reusable rocket system</em> that could <u>significantly reduce launch costs</u>.</p><h3>Revolutionary Technology:</h3><h4>How It Works:</h4><p>The <strong>innovative technology</strong> allows the rocket\'s first stage to return and land vertically after deployment, similar to landing an aircraft.</p><ul><li>üéØ <strong>Vertical Landing:</strong> Precision-guided touchdown</li><li><strong>Refurbishment:</strong> Quick turnaround for next mission</li><li><strong>Cost Reduction:</strong> Up to 70% cheaper than traditional rockets</li><li><strong>Environmental Benefits:</strong> Reduces space debris</li></ul><h3>Global Implications:</h3><p>This breakthrough positions the country among <em>elite spacefaring nations</em> with reusable launch capabilities:</p><ol><li><strong>USA:</strong> SpaceX Falcon 9</li><li><strong>China:</strong> Long March series</li><li><strong>India:</strong> Now joining the club üáÆüá≥</li></ol><h4>Future Applications:</h4><ul><li><strong>Commercial Satellite Launches:</strong> Affordable space access</li><li><strong>Space Tourism:</strong> Making space travel accessible</li><li><strong>Scientific Missions:</strong> More frequent deep space exploration</li><li><strong>National Security:</strong> Enhanced satellite deployment capabilities</li></ul><blockquote>"This is a game-changer for our space program. Reusability will accelerate our missions and make space more accessible for scientific and commercial purposes," said the ISRO Chairman.</blockquote><p>Scientists believe this will <strong>accelerate</strong> commercial space missions and satellite deployment programs. üåç</p>', 'article-2-1620564684.webp', '2021-05-08', 1, 1),
(45, 2, 10, 'Electric vehicle sales surge 150% in metropolitan cities', '<h2>üöó‚ö° Electric Vehicle Revolution: Sales Skyrocket</h2><p>Sales of <strong>electric vehicles</strong> have witnessed <em>exponential growth</em> in major urban centers, with a stunning <u>150% increase</u> compared to last year.</p><h3>Growth Drivers:</h3><ul><li>üå± <strong>Environmental Awareness:</strong> Consumers choosing eco-friendly options</li><li><strong>Government Incentives:</strong> Subsidies and tax benefits</li><li><strong>Lower Running Costs:</strong> Cheaper than petrol/diesel</li><li><strong>Better Technology:</strong> Improved battery range and performance</li></ul><h4>Market Expansion:</h4><p>Automobile manufacturers are <strong>expanding their EV portfolios</strong> to meet increasing demand:</p><ol><li><strong>Tata Motors:</strong> Nexon EV, Tigor EV</li><li><strong>Mahindra:</strong> eKUV100, eVerito</li><li><strong>Hyundai:</strong> Kona Electric, Ioniq 5</li><li><strong>MG Motor:</strong> ZS EV</li><li><strong>Ola Electric:</strong> Electric scooters</li></ol><h3>Infrastructure Development:</h3><p><strong>Charging infrastructure</strong> is rapidly being developed across cities:</p><ul><li>Public charging stations in malls and offices</li><li>Fast-charging corridors on highways</li><li>Home charging solutions</li><li>Battery swapping stations</li></ul><h4>Future Projections:</h4><blockquote>"The EV market is at a tipping point. With improving infrastructure and competitive pricing, electric vehicles will constitute 30% of total vehicle sales within the next five years," predicted industry analyst Rajesh Menon.</blockquote><p>The future is <em>electric</em> and <strong>sustainable</strong>! üåè</p>', 'article-2-1616580598.jpg', '2021-05-12', 0, 1),
(46, 3, 2, 'Regional cuisine festival celebrates culinary diversity', '<h2>üçΩÔ∏è Celebrating India\'s Culinary Heritage</h2><p>A <strong>month-long food festival</strong> showcasing <em>regional cuisines</em> from across the country opened today in the capital, bringing together the <u>diverse flavors of India</u>.</p><h3>Festival Highlights:</h3><h4>Participating Chefs:</h4><ul><li><strong>Over 200 chefs</strong> from different states</li><li>Traditional cooking demonstrations</li><li>Authentic recipes passed through generations</li><li>Live cooking competitions</li></ul><h4>Regional Specialties:</h4><p>Food enthusiasts can experience everything from <strong>Kashmir to Kanyakumari</strong>:</p><ol><li>üèûÔ∏è <strong>Kashmir:</strong> Wazwan - 36-course traditional feast</li><li><strong>Punjab:</strong> Makki di roti with sarson da saag</li><li><strong>Bengal:</strong> Machher jhol and mishti doi</li><li><strong>Kerala:</strong> Appam with stew</li><li><strong>Rajasthan:</strong> Dal baati churma</li><li><strong>Tamil Nadu:</strong> Chettinad delicacies</li><li><strong>Assam:</strong> Fish tenga and bamboo shoot curry</li><li><strong>Goa:</strong> Vindaloo and xacuti</li></ol><h3>Learning Opportunities:</h3><p>The festival also includes <em>educational components</em>:</p><ul><li><strong>Cooking Workshops:</strong> Hands-on learning sessions</li><li><strong>Masterclasses:</strong> By renowned culinary experts</li><li><strong>Cultural Performances:</strong> Traditional music and dance</li><li><strong>Recipe Books:</strong> Authentic regional recipes</li></ul><blockquote>"This festival is not just about food‚Äîit\'s about preserving our culinary heritage and celebrating the diversity that makes Indian cuisine so rich and unique," said Chef Sanjeev Kapoor.</blockquote><p>A true celebration of <strong>unity in diversity</strong>! üáÆüá≥</p>', 'article-3-1616581072.jpg', '2021-04-18', 1, 1),
(47, 3, 11, 'Ancient recipes get modern makeover in new cookbook', '<h2>üìñ Heritage Meets Innovation: New Cookbook Launches</h2><p>A celebrated chef has published a <strong>comprehensive cookbook</strong> reimagining <em>traditional recipes</em> with <u>contemporary techniques</u> and presentation styles.</p><h3>What\'s Inside:</h3><ul><li><strong>Over 150 Dishes:</strong> Spanning all meal categories</li><li>üç≥ <strong>Breakfast:</strong> Traditional meets modern</li><li><strong>Main Courses:</strong> Updated classics</li><li><strong>Desserts:</strong> Reinvented sweets</li></ul><h4>Special Features:</h4><p>Each recipe includes valuable context:</p><ol><li><strong>Historical Background:</strong> Origin stories and cultural significance</li><li><strong>Nutritional Information:</strong> Calories, proteins, vitamins</li><li><strong>Modern Techniques:</strong> Sous vide, air frying, molecular gastronomy</li><li><strong>Plating Suggestions:</strong> Restaurant-style presentation</li></ol><blockquote>"This book is my tribute to our culinary ancestors while embracing the possibilities of modern cooking. Tradition and innovation can coexist beautifully," says the author-chef.</blockquote><p>Food critics have praised the work for successfully <strong>bridging the gap</strong> between heritage and innovation in Indian cooking. üçΩÔ∏è</p>', 'article-3-1616581173.jpg', '2021-05-01', 0, 1),
(48, 4, 3, 'National education policy implementation gains momentum', '<h2>üéì New Education Policy: Schools Begin Transformation</h2><p>Schools and universities across the country have begun implementing <strong>key provisions</strong> of the <em>new education policy</em>, marking a <u>historic shift</u> in India\'s education system.</p><h3>Major Reforms:</h3><h4>Multidisciplinary Learning:</h4><ul><li><strong>Flexible Curriculum:</strong> Students can combine arts and sciences</li><li><strong>Multiple Entry/Exit:</strong> Credit-based system</li><li><strong>No Rigid Streams:</strong> Holistic education approach</li></ul><h4>Course Selection Flexibility:</h4><p>Students now have <em>unprecedented freedom</em> to choose subjects:</p><ol><li>Mix and match subjects across disciplines</li><li>Multiple majors and minors possible</li><li>Customized learning paths</li><li>Skill-based electives</li></ol><h4>Vocational Training Integration:</h4><ul><li>üîß <strong>Practical Skills:</strong> From Class 6 onwards</li><li><strong>Industry Partnerships:</strong> Real-world experience</li><li><strong>Employability Focus:</strong> Job-ready graduates</li></ul><h3>Implementation Progress:</h3><p>Educational institutions are <strong>restructuring curricula</strong> and training teachers for the new framework. This includes:</p><ul><li>Teacher training workshops</li><li>Curriculum redesign committees</li><li>Infrastructure upgrades</li><li>Assessment method changes</li></ul><blockquote>"The NEP represents a paradigm shift. It focuses on what students want to learn, not what we want to teach. This student-centric approach will transform Indian education," stated Education Secretary.</blockquote><p>Parents and educators have expressed <em>cautious optimism</em> about the potential long-term benefits for students. üìö</p>', 'article-4-1616582091.webp', '2021-04-22', 1, 1),
(49, 4, 12, 'Research shows significant learning gaps post-pandemic', '<h2>üìä Post-Pandemic Education Crisis: Massive Learning Losses</h2><p>A comprehensive study reveals <strong>substantial learning losses</strong> among students due to <em>prolonged school closures</em> during the pandemic.</p><h3>Key Research Findings:</h3><h4>Learning Loss Statistics:</h4><ul><li>üìâ <strong>Mathematics:</strong> Average 6-month learning loss</li><li><strong>Reading:</strong> 4-month deficit</li><li><strong>Science:</strong> 5-month gap</li><li><strong>Younger Students:</strong> Affected more severely</li></ul><h3>Digital Divide Reality:</h3><p>The research highlights <em>stark disparities</em> in access to digital learning resources:</p><h4>Urban vs Rural Gap:</h4><ol><li><strong>Urban Areas:</strong> 80% had online learning access</li><li><strong>Rural Areas:</strong> Only 35% had devices and internet</li><li><strong>Tribal Regions:</strong> Less than 20% connectivity</li><li><strong>Economic Factor:</strong> Low-income families most affected</li></ol><h3>Recommended Interventions:</h3><p>Education experts recommend <strong>targeted programs</strong> to help students catch up:</p><ul><li><strong>Remedial Classes:</strong> After-school tutoring</li><li><strong>Summer Programs:</strong> Intensive catch-up sessions</li><li><strong>Peer Learning:</strong> Student buddy systems</li><li><strong>Personalized Support:</strong> Identifying struggling students</li></ul><h4>Government Response:</h4><p>Governments are considering:</p><ol><li>Extending academic years</li><li>Introducing bridge courses</li><li>Hiring additional teachers</li><li>Providing tablets to students</li></ol><blockquote>"The pandemic has set back education by years. Without immediate intervention, an entire generation risks falling behind. We must act now with urgency and resources," warned lead researcher Dr. Malhotra.</blockquote>', 'article-4-1616582091.webp', '2021-05-04', 0, 1),
(50, 5, 4, 'Stock markets reach all-time high on positive economic indicators', '<h2>üìà Stock Markets Soar to Record Highs</h2><p>Major stock indices closed at <strong>record levels</strong> today, buoyed by <em>strong corporate earnings</em> and <u>optimistic economic forecasts</u>.</p><h3>Market Performance:</h3><h4>Leading Indices:</h4><ul><li>üü¢ <strong>Sensex:</strong> Crossed 52,000 mark (+2.3%)</li><li><strong>Nifty 50:</strong> Touched 15,600 levels (+2.1%)</li><li><strong>Midcap:</strong> Outperformed with 3.5% gains</li><li><strong>Smallcap:</strong> Rallied 4.2%</li></ul><h4>Sector-wise Winners:</h4><p>Banking and technology sectors led the <strong>market rally</strong>:</p><ol><li><strong>üè¶ Banking:</strong> Up 3.8% - NPA concerns easing</li><li><strong>üíª Technology:</strong> Gained 3.2% - Strong order books</li><li><strong>Pharmaceuticals:</strong> +2.7% - Export demand</li><li><strong>Auto:</strong> +2.4% - Festive season hopes</li><li><strong>Metals:</strong> +2.9% - Global demand surge</li></ol><h3>Investment Trends:</h3><p><strong>Foreign Institutional Investors (FIIs)</strong> have pumped substantial capital:</p><ul><li><strong>This Quarter:</strong> Rs 45,000 crores net investment</li><li><strong>Domestic Investors:</strong> Continued strong participation</li><li><strong>Mutual Funds:</strong> Record SIP inflows</li></ul><h4>Reasons for Bullish Trend:</h4><ol><li>Improving business sentiment</li><li>Government policy reforms supporting growth</li><li>Strong GDP recovery projections</li><li>Vaccination progress boosting confidence</li></ol><blockquote>"The market is reflecting the strong fundamentals of the Indian economy. Corporate earnings are robust, and the growth trajectory is promising. We expect this momentum to continue," said chief market analyst at a leading brokerage.</blockquote><p>Market analysts maintain a <em>positive outlook</em> for the coming quarters. üèÜ</p>', 'article-5-1620564561.jpeg', '2021-04-25', 1, 1),
(51, 5, 5, 'Startup ecosystem attracts record venture capital funding', '<h2>üöÄ Startup Boom: Record VC Funding in Q1</h2><p>Indian startups raised over <strong>$10 billion</strong> in <em>venture capital funding</em> in the first quarter, marking a <u>historic high</u> for the ecosystem.</p><h3>Funding Breakdown:</h3><h4>Sector-wise Investment:</h4><ul><li>üí≥ <strong>Fintech:</strong> $3.2 billion (32%)</li><li><strong>Edtech:</strong> $2.1 billion (21%)</li><li><strong>Healthtech:</strong> $1.8 billion (18%)</li><li><strong>E-commerce:</strong> $1.5 billion (15%)</li><li><strong>SaaS:</strong> $1.4 billion (14%)</li></ul><h4>Unicorn Creation:</h4><p>Several companies achieved <strong>unicorn status</strong> (ü¶Ñ valuation > $1 billion):</p><ol><li><strong>CRED:</strong> Fintech - $2.2B valuation</li><li><strong>PharmEasy:</strong> Healthtech - $1.5B valuation</li><li><strong>Meesho:</strong> Social Commerce - $2.1B valuation</li><li><strong>Groww:</strong> Investment Platform - $1.5B valuation</li><li><strong>Digit Insurance:</strong> Insurtech - $1.9B valuation</li></ol><h3>Investor Confidence:</h3><p>The funding surge reflects <em>strong investor confidence</em> in the entrepreneurial ecosystem:</p><ul><li><strong>Domestic VCs:</strong> Increased participation</li><li><strong>International Investors:</strong> Major funds entering</li><li><strong>Corporate VCs:</strong> Strategic investments</li><li><strong>Angel Networks:</strong> Active early-stage funding</li></ul><h4>Growth Drivers:</h4><ol><li>Digital adoption acceleration post-pandemic</li><li>Large addressable market</li><li>Skilled talent pool</li><li>Government support (Startup India)</li><li>Successful exit stories inspiring more founders</li></ol><blockquote>"India is witnessing a golden age of entrepreneurship. The combination of tech talent, market size, and capital availability is creating unprecedented opportunities. This momentum will continue as more international investors explore opportunities in emerging markets," said a managing partner at a leading VC firm.</blockquote><p>Industry leaders predict this momentum will continue throughout the year. üèÜ</p>', 'article-5-1620564561.jpeg', '2021-05-07', 1, 1),
(52, 6, 6, 'National cricket team announces squad for international tournament', '<h2>üèè Cricket Squad Unveiled for International Tournament</h2><p>The selection committee has unveiled the <strong>squad</strong> for the upcoming international cricket tournament featuring a <em>mix of experienced players</em> and <u>promising newcomers</u>.</p><h3>Squad Composition:</h3><h4>Batting Department:</h4><ul><li>üèÜ <strong>Openers:</strong> Rohit Sharma (c), Shikhar Dhawan</li><li><strong>Middle Order:</strong> Virat Kohli, Shreyas Iyer, Rishabh Pant (wk)</li><li><strong>All-rounders:</strong> Hardik Pandya, Ravindra Jadeja</li></ul><h4>Bowling Attack:</h4><ol><li><strong>Fast Bowlers:</strong> Jasprit Bumrah, Mohammed Shami, Bhuvneshwar Kumar</li><li><strong>Spinners:</strong> Yuzvendra Chahal, Kuldeep Yadav</li><li><strong>Backup:</strong> Shardul Thakur, Washington Sundar</li></ol><h3>New Faces:</h3><p>The team composition reflects a <strong>balanced approach</strong> with several <em>young talents</em>:</p><ul><li><strong>Prithvi Shaw:</strong> Explosive young opener</li><li><strong>Ishan Kishan:</strong> Dynamic wicket-keeper batsman</li><li><strong>Deepak Chahar:</strong> Swing bowling all-rounder</li></ul><h4>Strategic Balance:</h4><p>The squad offers:</p><ol><li>Strong batting depth - can bat till No. 9</li><li>Varied bowling options - pace and spin</li><li>Fielding excellence - athletic unit</li><li>Experience-youth balance</li></ol><blockquote>"We\'ve selected a squad that combines proven match-winners with exciting young talent. The team has the right balance and firepower for all conditions," said Chief Selector.</blockquote><p>Fans have reacted <em>positively</em> to the inclusion of several young talents. The tournament is scheduled to begin <strong>next month</strong> at multiple venues. üáÆüá≥</p>', 'article-6-1620565182.jpg', '2021-04-16', 0, 1);

